  "text": "14 Likely for this reason, the St Francis Heart trial is, unfortunately, largely ignored. [CITATION_1] However, the trial was underpowered, and in an exploratory post hoc analysis, subjects with CAC score >400 obtained benefit from statin therapy (8.7% versus 15.0% event rate; P=0.046). Given that ASCVD enjoys such a large proportion of federal research funding, it is surprising that these encouraging initial results have not been confirmed in a larger, more adequately powered contemporary study.",
